The easiest way is to use the directly the `textFieldExpression` (in your example use regex `&quot;&lt;[^&gt;]*&gt;&quot;` before printing text) es.


    &lt;textFieldExpression&gt;&lt;![CDATA[$F{field1}.replaceAll(&quot;&lt;[^&gt;]*&gt;&quot;, &quot;&quot;)]]&gt;&lt;/textFieldExpression&gt;

**Other solutions are:**

On the jasper `textField` you specify `markup=&quot;html&quot;`

Example:

    &lt;textField&gt;
	   &lt;reportElement x=&quot;0&quot; y=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; uuid=&quot;2cfd9640-f7ce-4bbe-a024-7b1b53d3b72b&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;textElement markup=&quot;html&quot;&gt;
		  &lt;paragraph lineSpacing=&quot;Single&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/textElement&gt;
		&lt;textFieldExpression&gt;&lt;![CDATA[$F{field1}]]&gt;&lt;/textFieldExpression&gt;
	&lt;/textField&gt;

This will process the text as if it was html, all text formatting code will work as es. `&lt;b&gt;Test&lt;/b&gt;` will result it **Test** and all none text formatting code will be removed (es. table, img ecc).

**Final solution**

If you still are not happy, you need more advanced code to format your text, the solution is **your own class** that format the text.

Simple example:

    &lt;textField&gt;
		&lt;reportElement x=&quot;0&quot; y=&quot;4&quot; width=&quot;100&quot; height=&quot;20&quot; uuid=&quot;2cfd9640-f7ce-4bbe-a024-7b1b53d3b72b&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;textElement markup=&quot;none&quot;&gt;
		 &lt;paragraph lineSpacing=&quot;Single&quot;/&gt;
		&lt;/textElement&gt;
		&lt;textFieldExpression&gt;&lt;![CDATA[com.my.package.JasperReportTextHandler.format($F{field1})]]&gt;&lt;/textFieldExpression&gt;
	&lt;/textField&gt;

Create the java class `JasperReportTextHandler` in package `com.my.package` with static method:

    class JasperReportTextHandler{
      public static String format(String value){
       //... do your stuff regEx, split...
       return value;
      }
    }

Just be sure that the `JasperReportTextHandler` is in class path when you execute the report.

Have Fun

